snippet.title: 1st Test Day 1 | Highlights | Sri Lanka Tour Of England | 21st August 2024
snippet.description:
England and Sri Lanka faced each other for the 1st Test at the Emirates Old Trafford, Manchester. Sri Lanka lost some early wickets against a mighty England bowling attack. However, Sri Lanka managed to put up a respectable total of 236 runs on the board before getting all out. Dhananjaya de Silva and Milan Rathnayaka shined with the bat, while Chris Woakes and Shoaib Bashir did the damage with the ball. Later, England batted for 4 overs in which their openers scored 22 runs.
.
.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: 5th T20I | Highlights | New Zealand Women Tour Of England | 17th July 2024
snippet.description:
In the 5th and final T20I, England Women won the match by 20 runs and sealed the series 5 - 0. England was put to bat first and they scored 155 runs for the loss of 7 wickets. Heather Knight shined with the bat thanks to a vital 46-run knock. New Zealand however could not chase down the total and ended their batting with 135 runs, while Lauren Bell picked up a three-wicket haul for England.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: 2nd T20I | Highlights | Pakistan Tour Of England | 25th May 2024
snippet.description:
In the 2nd T20I of the Pakistan Tour Of England, the hosts set a target of 183, with Jos Buttler's scintillating 84 runs off 51 balls leading the charge. Shaheen Afridi's impressive bowling, with 3 wickets at an economy of 9, kept Pakistan in the contest. However, England's bowlers, spearheaded by Reece Topley who also claimed 3 wickets, managed to restrict Pakistan to 160 runs. Despite Fakhar Zaman's explosive 45 runs off 21 balls, Pakistan fell short by 23 runs.
.

snippet.title: Master 11 vs Khiladi 11 | Highlights | ISPL | 6th March 2024
snippet.description:
Watch the highlights of the inaugural match between Sachin Tendulkar's Master 11 and Akshay Kumar's Khiladi 11 in the Indian Street Premier League 2024. Sachin Tendulkar's Master 11 scored 94 runs in 10 overs and lost 7 wickets in the process. Sachin was the top scorer with 30 runs. Akshay Kumar's Khiladi 11 then put up a strong performance during the chase but lost the match by 5 runs in the end. 

Master 11: Sachin Tendulkar, Amir, Suresh Raina, Yusuf Pathan, Stuart Binny, Rishabh Chavan, Munaf Patel, Ram Charan, Kunal Khemmu, Samir Kochhar, Elvish Yadav.

Khiladi 11: Akshay Kumar, Suriya, Irfan Pathan, Robin Uthappa, Praveen Kumar, Naman Ojha, Gaurav Taneja, Prateik Babbar, Sukhwinder Singh, Munawar Farooqui, Riyaz Ali.

snippet.title: Emotional Olympic gold medal victory after 12 years! - Oscar Figueroa 🥇🇨🇴 | Never Give Up!🔥
snippet.description:
📲 Want to watch live sport and original documentaries for free? Check out our website: https://oly.ch/WatchLiveSport

Oscar Albeiro Figueroa Mosquera is a Colombian weightlifter who competes in the 62 kg class. At the 2004 Olympic Games, he finished fifth in the 56 kg class with a total of 280 kg. In 2008 in Beijing, he struggled with a serious injury that prevented him from achieving a result. After a successful operation, he returned in 2012, set an Olympic record of 177 kg in the clean and jerk and won silver. He finally won gold in Rio in 2016 with a total of 318 kg and then retired from the sport by symbolically taking off his shoes and placing them on the platform. 🏅👟

📲 Want to watch live sport and original documentaries for free? Check out our website: https://oly.ch/WatchLiveSport

Oscar Albeiro Figueroa Mosquera is a Colombian weightlifter who competes in the 62 kg class. At the 2004 Olympic Games, he finished fifth in the 56 kg class with a total of 280 kg. In 2008 in Beijing, he struggled with a serious injury that prevented him from achieving a result. After a successful operation, he returned in 2012, set an Olympic record of 177 kg in the clean and jerk and won silver. He finally won gold in Rio in 2016 with a total of 318 kg and then retired from the sport by symbolically taking off his shoes and placing them on the platform. 🏅👟

snippet.title: Olympic medal win after 24 Years - Nick Skelton 🥇🇬🇧 | Never Give Up!🔥
snippet.description:
📲 Want to watch live sport and original documentaries for free? Check out our website: https://oly.ch/WatchLiveSport

Nick Skelton is a former British show jumper who ended his successful career on April 5, 2017 at the age of 59. He started riding at the age of 18 months and won an individual gold medal and two team silver medals at the 1975 European Junior Championships. Skelton took part in the European Show Jumping Championships for 26 years and won a total of nine medals, including three gold medals. He achieved his greatest successes at the Olympic Games: in 2012 he won team gold for Great Britain, and in 2016 he won the individual gold medal with his horse Big Star. Shortly after the 2016 Olympics, Skelton retired with Big Star. 🏇🏻🏅

snippet.title: Anthony Jeanjean secures top spot at Shanghai 2024! 🏆🇫🇷 | #OlympicQualifierSeries
snippet.description:
📺 Re-live ALL the incredible #Paris2024 action ➡️ https://go.olympics.com/watch
A storming opening run saw Anthony Jeanjean take first place in the BMX freestyle park men's final at the Olympic Qualifier Series Shanghai on Saturday (18 May).

Big things were expected of the in-form Frenchman, who sealed a World Cup win in Montpellier last week.

Unperturbed by the rising temperatures in the midday sun at another sold-out Huangpu Riverside OQS Urban Park arena, he executed flips, handle bar spins, and tail spins with blistering speed for a first run score of 93.54.

Olympic champion Logan Martin of Australia struggled to find rhythm in the first run, but showing his champion credentials, roared back to life with a score of 92.65 to finish second.

Great Britain's reigning world champion Kieran Reilly, a noticeably more muscle-bound athlete than his rivals, used that power to gain huge air and deep gasps from the crowd on his jumps, for third.

snippet.title: #TheFirstEffect | Firsts move the world forward.
snippet.description:
They help make the inconceivable achievable and pave the way for others to follow. ​

It took decades for the first runner to break the 4-minute mile, then 16 runners achieved it within the next year. Sarah Attar ran alone for the last 32s of her race at London 2012, but as Saudi Arabia’s first-ever female Olympic runner, she set a precedent for thousands of female athletes to follow.​

As the Worldwide Management Consulting Partner of the IOC, we’re using our global scale, deep insights, and understanding of innovation to track the impact of firsts at the Olympic and Paralympic Games.​

Explore #TheFirstEffect to see how firsts move the world forward.

snippet.title: The fastest man in Africa - Ferdinand Omanyala 🇰🇪 | The Starting Line x @TOYOTAglobal
snippet.description:
📺 Re-live ALL the incredible #Paris2024 action ➡️ https://go.olympics.com/watch 

#TheStartingLine, presented by Toyota. 
Head over to our website to watch all the episodes early: https://oly.ch/TheStartingLineyt 

In pursuit of their 2024 Olympic dreams, our athletes embark on a reflective journey. Surrounded by the beauty of their homeland, their friends, family or community, they seek inspiration and purpose from the people and places that nurtured their passion. Along the way, they share their stories, mentor local youths and create a powerful ripple effect of motivation, leaving a lasting impact on the next generation.

Known as the ‘Fastest Man in Africa’ for his prowess in the 100m, Ferdinand Omanyala is setting his sights on becoming the fastest man in the world this summer. We follow him as he travels back to his hometown of Kitale to get the blessings he needs from his peers and uncover the remarkable story of his origins.

Enjoy the journey of Ferdinand Omanyala 🇰🇪, Africa's record-holder and the ninth-fastest man in history. With a time of 9.77 seconds in the 100m event, set in 2021, in Nairobi, Omanyala etched his name into the track and field history. Join us as we explore the life of Omanyala, his roots, his parenting, his setbacks and his relentless pursuit of excellence on and off the track. 🏃🏾♂️💨 

#Paris2024 | #TheStartingLine | #StartYourImpossible | #Toyota | @toyotausa | @TOYOTAglobal

snippet.title: Manon Claeys' 🇧🇪 path to equestrian glory | The Starting Line x @TOYOTAglobal
snippet.description:
#TheStartingLine, presented by Toyota. 
Head over to our website to watch all the episodes early: https://oly.ch/TheStartingLineyt 

In pursuit of their 2024 Olympic dreams, our athletes embark on a reflective journey. Surrounded by the beauty of their homeland, their friends, family or community, they seek inspiration and purpose from the people and places that nurtured their passion. Along the way, they share their stories, mentor local youths and create a powerful ripple effect of motivation, leaving a lasting impact on the next generation.

A Para equestrian athlete from Belgium, Manon Claeys shares her journey back from severe injury to competition. After her accident, she thought she would never ride a horse again. Now, together with her cherished horse Katarina, she trains surrounded by her team and family to achieve a gold medal in Paris.

Discover the inspiring journey of Manon Claeys 🇧🇪, a Paralympic equestrian athlete hailing from Belgium. In 2007, a riding accident left her with a broken neck and three spinal fractures. Initially doubting she would ever ride again, she defied the odds and got back on her horse. At the 2020 Summer Paralympics, she triumphed, winning bronze medals in both dressage competitions🥉🥉. Find out more about Claeys' story, her deep bond with Katarina 🐎 and her unique relationship with her trainer and family. 

#Paris2024 | #TheStartingLine | #StartYourImpossible | #Toyota | @toyota  | @TOYOTAglobal

Welcome to #Gangwon2024! The 4th Winter Youth Olympic Games will take place in the province of Gangwon in the Republic of Korea, which already hosted the Olympic Winter Games #PyeongChang2018. snippet.description:
Find out more about Gangwon 2024: https://oly.ch/3ZBEoxo 

The countdown begins to #Gangwon2024! 🎿 

We're live from Athens, Greece as the torch lighting ceremony for the next #YouthOlympics kicks off the torch's journey to South Korea!

The 4th Winter Youth Olympic Games will take place in the province of Gangwon in the Republic of Korea, which already hosted the Olympic Winter Games PyeongChang 2018. These first Winter YOG to be held in Asia will build on the Olympic Games legacy and engage even more young people through various activities before, throughout and after the Games.

The vision of Gangwon 2024 is to let the youth celebrate peaceful coexistence and unity through sport to create a better future together. The aim is to drive positive change and social unity in the region, impacting society in the areas of sport, culture and education. Gangwon 2024 will benefit from many of the facilities used for PyeongChang 2018. This will ensure a cost-efficient and sustainable YOG, and, at the same time, provide the participating athletes with the opportunity to compete in some of the same sites as Olympians did a few years before.

snippet.title: Closest swimming finish EVER! Ft. Michael Phelps ⏱️
snippet.description:
📺 Re-live ALL the incredible #Paris2024 action ➡️ https://go.olympics.com/watch 

📲 Subscribe to @olympics: http://oly.ch/Subscribe 

In the thrilling finale of the 100m butterfly event at the Beijing 2008 Olympics, Michael Phelps left the world awestruck with an astonishingly close finish. As the race reached its climax, Phelps engaged in an intense battle with Serbian swimmer Milorad Čavić. Stroke by stroke, they surged toward the wall, both determined to touch it first. With hearts pounding and spectators holding their breath, the outcome remained uncertain until the very last moment. 

In the end, Phelps managed to stretch his arm 4.7mm further forward and take the victory by just one hundredth of a second. This thrilling race went down in swimming history as one of the closest finishes and cemented Michael Phelps' legendary status in the world of competitive swimming.

snippet.title: 🇮🇳 Who are the stars to watch at #Paris2024? | Pride of India
snippet.description:
📺 Re-live ALL the incredible #Paris2024 action ➡️ https://go.olympics.com/watch 

📲 Subscribe to @olympics: http://oly.ch/Subscribe 

At the Olympic Games in Tokyo 2020, several Indian athletes won medals:

Mirabai Chanu won a silver medal in weightlifting in the women's 49kg category, securing India's first medal at the Games.
Lovlina Borgohain won a bronze medal in women's welterweight boxing (64-69kg) category, marking her debut at the Olympics.
PV Sindhu won a bronze medal in women's singles badminton, becoming the first Indian woman and second Indian athlete overall to win two individual Olympic medals.
Ravi Kumar Dahiya won a silver medal in men's 57kg freestyle wrestling, securing India's second silver medal in wrestling after Sushil Kumar's silver in 2012.
The Indian Men's Hockey Team won a bronze medal in men's hockey, ending India's 41-year wait for an Olympic medal in hockey since their last gold in 1980.
Bajrang Punia won a bronze medal in men's 65kg freestyle wrestling, becoming the third Indian debutant to win a medal at the Tokyo 2020 Olympics.
Neeraj Chopra won a historic gold medal in men's javelin throw, becoming the first Indian to win a gold medal in athletics at the Olympics. His gold medal marked a significant achievement for India.

These Indian athletes brought glory to the nation and showcased their exceptional skills and determination at the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games. But who are the stars to watch at #Paris2024?

snippet.title: Joe Choong - Men's Modern Pentathlon | Reigning Champions
snippet.description:
📲 Subscribe to @olympics: http://oly.ch/Subscribe 

Joseph Choong, a British modern pentathlete, won the gold medal at the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games. This was a historic moment for Team GB as Choong became the first British man to win an Olympic gold medal in modern pentathlon since the event's introduction to the Olympic program in 1912. Choong's victory was also a sensational one, as he set an Olympic record in the process.

Choong's performance was impressive, as he started the final event, the combined running and shooting discipline, in sixth place but quickly moved up the ranks to secure the gold medal.

Overall, Joseph Choong's victory in the modern pentathlon event at the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games was a historic moment for British sports, as he became the first British man to win an Olympic gold medal in the event in over a century.

snippet.title: The first EVER women's 100m final!
snippet.description:
📲 Subscribe to @olympics: http://oly.ch/Subscribe 

First women’s track Olympic champion 1928 at the Olympic Games in Amsterdam.
Robinson competed in her first meet only four months before the 1928 Olympic Games. In her first outdoor meet, she set a world record for 100m. The 1928 100m was the first women's track event to be contested in Olympic history. Robinson won the final by half a metre in what was only her fourth track meet ever. She also earned a silver medal in the 4x100m relay.
Three years after her Olympic triumph, Robinson was badly injured in an airplane crash. The man who found her thought she was dead, so he put her in his car trunk and drove her to a mortician. She was unconscious for seven weeks and she could not walk normally for two years…but she did survive. Robinson wanted to return to competitive sprinting, but she was no longer able to bend her leg fully at the knee, so she could not assume the crouched starting position. She could, however, run in relays. In 1936, Betty Robinson won a second gold medal as a member of the U.S. 4x100m relay team.

snippet.title: 88 Years later... 🤯 | Women's Javelin Then and Now!
snippet.description:
📲 Want to watch live sport and original documentaries for free? Check out our website: https://oly.ch/WatchLiveSport

The perfection of the technique behind the Javelin over the past decades is outstanding! The javelin throw was already part of the Olympic Games in ancient times and was first included in the program of the Intermediate Olympic Games in 1906 as the "freestyle javelin throw". Today's javelin throw has been part of the Olympic Games for men since 1908 and for women since 1932.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: One of the greatest: Carl Lewis' long jump successes 🤩
snippet.description:
📲 Want to watch live sport and original documentaries for free? Check out our website: https://oly.ch/WatchLiveSport

Carl Lewis is an American former track and field athlete. He is one of the most successful track and field athletes in the history of sport. He set several world records and dominated the sprint and long jump between 1983 and 1996 with nine Olympic victories and eight world championship titles. In 1999, he was honored by World Athletics as Athlete of the Century. 🏅
He won the gold medal in the long jump in Los Angeles in 1984 with a distance of 8.54m. In Seoul 1988 with 8.41m, in Barcelona 1992 with 8.67m and in Atlanta 1996 with 8.50m he won the gold medal. 🤯

snippet.title: David Raum is the Mannschaft's new shooting star 🇩🇪
snippet.description:
📲 Subscribe to @olympics: http://oly.ch/Subscribe

snippet.title: Neeraj Chopra reacts to his Tokyo 2020 gold medal performance! | Olympic ⏮ Rewind
snippet.description:
📲 Subscribe to @olympics: http://oly.ch/Subscribe 

Welcome to Olympic Rewind, the series where Olympians re-watch their iconic Olympic performances, and give us hilarious reactions, insightful commentary and a unique behind-the-scenes perspective on competing at the Olympics. 𝗧𝗼𝗱𝗮𝘆'𝘀 𝗲𝗽𝗶𝘀𝗼𝗱𝗲: Olympic Javelin champion, Neeraj Chopra 🇮🇳

On August 7th 2021, India’s @NeerajChopra1 became only the second individual Indian athlete after Abhinav Bindra to be crowned Olympic champion as he won gold in the men’s javelin throw at the Tokyo Olympics on Saturday.

The gold medal is also India’s first Olympic medal in track-and-field events. It took India’s medal count at Tokyo 2020 to seven - their best-ever haul at a single Olympics. Neeraj Chopra threw a best attempt of 87.58m to win the Olympic gold. Czech Republic’s Jakub Vadlejch won silver and fellow Czech Vitezslav Vesely won bronze to complete the podium.

As the birthplace of a global hip-hop movement, we meet some of the pioneers of Breaking in New-York City. While Kid Glyde shares his passion for breaking with the next generation at his Harlem studio, three thousand miles away in Anchorage Alaska, B-Boy Icey Ives, two-time US national champion, melts the ice with his local crew Frozen Flow while being a community leader, a teacher and a role model for the youth living in extremely challenging conditions.

Discover the world of breaking through the eyes of five young dancers practicing this new Olympic sport around the globe. What does it mean to be a B-Girl or a B-Boy today? snippet.description:

Join us as into the journeys of Brianna Rollins 🇺🇸 and Jasmine Camacho-Quinn 🇵🇷 at the Olympics. While Brianna Rollins secured gold at the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics with a time of 12.48 seconds, Jasmine Camacho-Quinn made history at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics. She clinched the gold medal in the 100 meters hurdles, setting a personal best and Olympic record of 12.26 seconds in the semi-finals. snippet.title: 🇬🇧  Dave Ryding, from ‘dry’ ski slopes to an Olympic medal? ⛷ | Athletes to Watch - Beijing 2022
snippet.description:
📲 Subscribe to @olympics: http://oly.ch/Subscribe 

 Slalom skier Dave Ryding has reached the pinnacle of the sport, but his journey was anything but traditional. Growing up in Lancashire, Dave spent the first 14 years of his ski career training and competing on plastic ‘dry’ ski slopes. Beijing 2022 will be Dave’s final Olympics. Will his experience and form be enough to win a rare medal for Great Britain?

snippet.title: 🇵🇷 Transplant Survivor to Represent Puerto-Rico at next Olympics I Winter Tracks Ep. 1
snippet.description:
📲 Subscribe to @olympics: http://oly.ch/Subscribe 

 When William Flaherty was just three years old, he had a bone marrow transplant to save his life from a rare form of cancer. The donor that saved his life was his brother, Charles. Charles went on to be the first Winter Olympian to represent Puerto Rico in two decades and competed in PyeongChang 2018. Now aged 17, William is preparing to take over for his brother in representing his country at the next Winter Olympic Games.

There is no one road to the Olympic Games. Every four years athletes are brought together from all corners of the world, and all walks of life, with unique journeys but a shared dream. snippet.title: 🏒 Ice Hockey superstar raised on a farm searching for Olympic glory!
snippet.description:
📲 Subscribe to @olympics: http://oly.ch/Subscribe 

 Jenni Hiirikoski is regarded as one of the finest Ice Hockey players of her generation. She is the captain of Finland’s national team and a future Hall of Famer. Until she was a teenager, Jenni had to play with boys. Later whilst her teammates went on to the NHL, Jenni had to balance competing with working a day job despite being one of the best players ever. She now goes into her fourth Olympics in Beijing knowing it could be her last chance to achieve Olympic glory.

There is no one road to the Olympic Games. Every four years athletes are brought together from all corners of the world, and all walks of life, with unique journeys but a shared dream. snippet.title: 🏆UN DIA DE FINAL! 🔥 Champions of Europe
snippet.description:
Patri Guijarro (2) and Fridolina Rolfö mount a spectacular comeback after going 2-0 down to win a second continental title in Eindhoven.

The city has a place in Barça hearts forever. Because that is where the women have won their second Champions League! And they did it in epic fashion. The spectre of Turin twelve months ago hung over the game as they found themselves trailing Wolfsburg by two goals at half time. But they did what they failed to do a year ago and produced a spectacular comeback that people will be talking about for years.

snippet.title: Real Madrid win first LaLiga match of the season!
snippet.description:
Real Madrid started their 23/24 LaLiga campaign with a 0-2 win at San Mamés against Athletic Club. Ancelotti's team got off on the right foot in the league and in the match in Bilbao as well, with Rodrygo opening the scoring in the 28th minute and becoming Real Madrid's first goalscorer of the season. The win at San Mamés was secured with a debut golazo from Jude Bellingham just eight minutes later. Join us for an exclusive peek into the Real Madrid dressing room as well, with the team going out on to the pitch with a special t-shirt sending encouragement to Thibaut Courtois. Real Madrid's next match is on August 19 against Almería.

snippet.title: Almería 1-3 Real Madrid | HIGHLIGHTS | LaLiga 2023/24
snippet.description:
Real Madrid won their second match in a row at the start of LaLiga after beating Almería at the Power Horse Stadium (Almería 1-3 Real Madrid) . It was Almería that opened the scoring with an early goal by former Real Madrid youth team player Sergio Arribas, but new LaLiga darling Jude Bellingham equalled the score with a stunning goal in the 19th minute. Carlo Ancelotti’s team looked for the full comeback and it was Bellingham again who got on the scoresheet in the 60th minute with a header. Vini Jr. sent a rocket in the back of the net in the 73rd minute to complete the scoreline.
#AlmeríaRealMadrid | #LaLigaHighlights

snippet.title: KARIM BENZEMA BALLON D'OR 2022 | Real Madrid
snippet.description:
Karim Benzema has been crowned as the top-performing player in world football in 2022. The Real Madrid skipper was recognised as the best player in the world and collected the Ballon d’Or in Paris. France Football, which awards the coveted prize, recognised his outstanding year at a ceremony at which our club was well represented in an expedition headed up by president Florentino Pérez. Benzema saw off competition from Sadio Mané, Kevin De Bruyne and Lewandowski (in that order) in voting that involved 180 international journalists, who cast their votes on the basis of the achievements of each player during the 2021/22 season.
#BallondOr

snippet.title: Celta 1-4 Real Madrid | HIGHLIGHTS | LaLiga 2022/23
snippet.description:
Watch all the goals and highlights from Real Madrid’s second LaLiga 2022/23 match of the season (Celta de Vigo 1-4 Real Madrid). Sit back and enjoy as Carlo Ancelotti and his men defeated Celta courtesy of goals from Benzema (penalty) Modrić (a fine strike from distance), Vini Jr. and Valverde. Iago Aspas quickly equalized the game for Celta in the first half as Celta were then awarded a penalty before Luka Modrić’s wonder goal minutes before half-time. Vini Jr. and Valverde grabbed the final two goals for the madridistas, who picked up a second consecutive away win.
#CeltaRealMadrid | #LaLigaHighlights

snippet.title: THANK YOU, MARCELO | Real Madrid Legend
snippet.description:

Marcelo, who joined Real Madrid from Fluminense in 2006, leaves the club as the most decorated player in Real Madrid history. Truly a legend, having picked up 25 titles. Marcelo’s impressive list of Real Madrid honours includes 5 Champions League titles, 4 Club World Cup titles, 3 UEFA Super Cups, 6 LaLiga titles, 2 Copas del Rey and 5 Spanish Super Cups. Thank you, captain.

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Chelsea 1-3 Real Madrid | UEFA Champions League
snippet.description:
Enjoy the goals and highlights from a THRILLING evening at Stamford Bridge as Real Madrid produced a majestic performance to defeat Chelsea 3-1 in their Champions League quarter-final first leg, thanks to a brilliant Karim Benzema hat-trick (Chelsea 1-3 Real Madrid). Benzema scored twice in quick succession in the first half before Kai Havertz cut the deficit for Chelsea. However, Benzema scored once more shortly after the break to extend the advantage for Carlo Ancelotti's side and give them a commanding lead ahead of next week's second leg at the Santiago Bernabéu.
#UCL

snippet.title: Real Madrid are all set for the Copa del Rey!
snippet.description:
Step on to the Ciudad Real Madrid training pitch with Zinedine Zidane's Real Madrid players and see first-hand how they carried out their final preparations before Wednesday's opening Copa del Rey match against Alcoyano at El Collao in the last 32 of the competition. Zidane has called up the following 20 players for the clash in Alicante.
Goalkeepers: Courtois, Lunin and Altube.
Defenders: E. Militão, Nacho, Marcelo, Odriozola, F. Mendy and Chust.
Midfielders: Kroos, Casemiro, Valverde, Isco and Blanco.
Forwards: Hazard, Benzema, Asensio, Lucas V., Vini Jr. and Mariano.

snippet.title: The #LALIGA fight continues! | Granada 1-4 Real Madrid | BTS
snippet.description:
Real Madrid's fight for the LaLiga title continues following a comprehensive 4-1 win away at Granada on Thursday. Join the team, including coach Zinedine Zidane, top scorer Karim Benzema and Casemiro, as they travelled from Madrid to the Andalusian city and follow their pre-match preparations and post-match declarations. Luka Modrić opened the scoring, which was doubled when Rodrygo netted just before the break. Jorge Molina reduced the deficit for the hosts but strikes in quick succession from Álvaro Odriozola and Karim Benzema sealed an impressive win for Zidane's men, who will continue their LaLiga title fight at Athletic Club on Sunday.
